sentences: Katherine Needleman (born May 14, 1978) is the principal oboist of the Baltimore Symphony Orchestra in the United States.
She was the first prize winner of the Gillet-Fox International Oboe Competition of the International Double Reed Society in 2003.
Needleman joined the oboe faculty of the Peabody Institute of the Johns Hopkins University in 2005.
In 2019, she filed a rape and discrimination complaint against concertmaster Jonathan Carney.
